name: willow stem cutting production, for planting | willow stem cutting, for planting | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/7101/documentation

This dataset represents the production of 1 piece of willow stem cutting. The moisture content at storage is 48%. The average weight of one piece is 20g (fresh matter). The yield is 100'000 stem cuttings per hectare.

This activity represents the production of 1 piece of stem cutting of willow for planting, based on the expenditures of willow growing during 1 season including the establishment and operation of the plantation. The inputs of mineral fertilisers, seed and pesticides are considered. It is assumed that no organic fertilisers are applied.


The dataset includes all machine operations and corresponding inputs of machine infrastructure and sheds. Machine operations are: soil cultivation, planting, fertilisation, weed control, pest and pathogen control, harvest, transport of stem cuttings from field to farm (2 km), and storage in a cold storage house during 1.5 months. Further, direct field emissions are included. This activity ends after cold storage of stem cuttings at the farm gate.
category: A:Agriculture, forestry and fishing/01:Crop and animal production, hunting and related service activities/013:Plant propagation/0130:Plant propagation

processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription: Electricity consumption and infrastructure for cold storage house were extrapolated from the dataset 'potato seed production, Swiss integrated production, for setting".
processDocumentation.samplingDescription:
The inventories were generated on the basis of data from the 'GruBE' project (Hölscher et al. 2007) and complemented with information from expert estimates, extension service documents and literature. The sources used in the project were KTBL (2006), Agrobränsle (2005), Hofmann (1998), Textor (2006) and personal communications from producers. --- Sources: Hölscher T., Deinmling S., Freiermuth Knuchel R., Gaillard G., Kägi T. & Müller-Sämann K. (2007) Energieoptionen aus landwirtschaftlicher Biomasse am Oberrhein - Auswirkungen für Landwirtschaft und Umwelt - Endbericht zum Projekt. Agentur für Nachhaltige Nutzung von Agrarlandschaften (ANNA). Müllheim, Germany. --- KTBL (2006) Energiepflanzen. Daten für die Planung des Energiepflanzenanbaus. Kuratorium für Technik und Bauwesen in der Landwirtschaft, Darmstadt, 372 p. --- Agrogbänsle (2005) Manual Salix viminalis. Ackerbauliche Informationen zum Weidenanbau. Informationsblatt der Firma Agrobränsle. Örebro, Sweden, 5 p. --- Hofmann M. (1998) Bewirtschaftung schnellwachsender Baumarten auf landwirtschaftlichen Flächen Kurzumtrieb. Merkblatt 11 des Forschungsinstituts für schnellwachsende Baumarten. Hann. Münden (ed.), 22 S. --- Textor B. (2006) Die Ernte forstlicher Rohstoffe auf landwirtschaftlichen Flächen im Kurzumtrieb. In: LAP, Landesanstalt für Pflanzenbau Forchheim (2006):Pflanzliche Rohstoffe zur
energetischen Nutzung. Workshop am 4.06.2006, Rheinstetten.

exchanges.description: Total amount of active substance/s of pesticides needed for the production of willow stem cutting, for planting is calculated to be circa 2.33E-05 kg. Pesticide/s used in this dataset is/are: 'acetamide-anillide-compound, unspecified', 'glyphosate', 'pesticide, unspecified'. The total amount of active substance/s is doubled in order to account for the packaging of the dilluted product of pesticide/s that is/are applied. Therefore, 4.65E-05 kg of packaging for pesticides is justified with this exchange.
